wikipedia_page.main: Gavin Kelly (born 29 September 1968) is an English former footballer, born in Beverley, who played as a goalkeeper in the Football League for Hull City, Bristol Rovers and Scarborough, and in the Hong Kong First Division League for Golden. He also played non-League football for clubs including North Ferriby United, Harrogate Town, Whitby Town, Bradford Park Avenue, and Bridlington Town.
